**Effective Java Item 45 — Use streams judiciously:**

**Streams are WORSE for:**
```java
// ❌ Modifying external state
List<String> results = new ArrayList<>();
stream.forEach(x -> results.add(transform(x))); // side effect!
// ✅ Use collector
List<String> results = stream.map(this::transform).collect(toList());

// ❌ Need early termination with complex condition
// Traditional loop with break is clearer

// ❌ Multiple return values or exception handling
// Streams can't throw checked exceptions
```

**Streams are BETTER for:**
- Transform sequences: `map`, `flatMap`
- Filter: `filter`, `takeWhile`
- Combine: `reduce`, `collect`
- Search: `findFirst`, `anyMatch`
- Group: `groupingBy`, `partitioningBy`
